reviews.text: I was lucky enough to visit the Bellevue House during the Canada 150 celebration, where there was free admission. It is a truly beautiful location with a wonderfully maintained property including apple trees and gardens. Staff were very friendly and loved explaining the history of the area.

The house itself was unfortunately closed for maintainence and restorative work the day I visited. But you get to check out the grounds and gardens yourself if you wish.

There is also a small theatre where you can watch a little video about history and background of the place.

Yes- I would go there again.

One of my favourite historic sites. Despite the fact that the house itself is under construction, their interpreters managed to keep the kids occupied for a full hour with old-time games. The grounds and the gardens are beautiful and they’ve done a great job with the interpretation center.

This National Historic Site is a must see.  Home of our 1st Prime Minister.  Staff is very knowledgeable.  A wonderful place to take your child to.  We spent about 1 hour there. Free parking & there is a bus/trolley that stops at the site too. Knowledge is the key to your child's development. My son really enjoyed this place.
Staff are very friendly and the grounds are vey pretty.😍 very nice place to be. I would definitely recommend this place

Pretty, even though the locks were dry and the museum closed. On this visit we ventured down both sides of the highway - on one side you can walk along the locks to a pier where you often find people fishing. On the other side of the highway there is a levy which we walked on to the end. Loads of geese so you have to watch where you walk, but otherwise a great view and nice place to sightsee and take your dog.  There are picnic tables available so it would be a wonderful place to stop for lunch in the nicer weather.
Nice spot. An unexpected place on a surprise visit. Must be lovely in summer

Absolutely amazing location. Love the old manual style lock system. Great place for a weddings and photos! Make sure you check out the little museum as there is all sorts of neat stuff in there. My favourite place to visit when on trips to Ottawa.
You will find perfect Old bridges with high technical engineered way for transfer boats from low levels to higher and beautiful park
Historical part of Kingston on the Rideau Canal system. Great place to go for a picnic and watch the boats come and go. Interesting artifacts and history to take in.

Loved the historic cathedral architecture, we spent nearly 2 hrs looking at the amazing craftsmanship of the glass artists near the prayer area. Calm & peaceful environment brings out the pleasantness in you.
One of the finest Cathedrals in Canada.
It's a beautiful building with dedicated learners.
Beautiful church and great mass

Roadtrip. Magnificent church! Probably the tallest building in Kingston, cathedral gives a strong feeling of peace and faith. The atmosphere is airy and the scent of the candles makes this place right for any person of any faith. My personal favorite is a small chapel at at the back part of the cathedral. Overall impression is: Great active church with a true spirit of Christianity.
Unfortunately was closed for the season so we could only see the outside. It would be nice if it had stayed open a couple weeks into September instead of closing after labour day.
Very cool piece of history. You can wander through the entire place and it's beautifully restored. A must see!
Very cool experiance
Well laid out and informative. Good value for only $5

People throw their garbage into the  moat around the tower, making it unsightly and dirty.  Put up netting to prevent this or get park staff to clean it up maybe.   There are plenty of garbage cans in the area, but they were also crammed full so not really preventing the filth.  The area used to be much better taken care of.

Beautiful campus.

As regards individual modules, lectures and tutorials, students should ask if they are being taught by permanent lecturers, PhD students or by individuals on other contracts etc. Ask about the type of contract (and how long or short is it).

In my opinion, ALL teaching and related activities such as grading/marking should be undertaken by staff of at least lecturer grade and only delegated to others when completely necessary (e.g. to cover sickness).
Peaceful place! Botanic gardens are really near, which makes it pleasant to make a break from studies

I was in this university in 60’s and happened to be in the student union (men) committee.it was during this period ladies and gentlemen unions merged into one union. A modern block of building was opened just in front of the main entrance of the university. I remember Saturday hops and snooker tables in the union. My most memorable time was playing in dramas in Whitla Hall and freshers week. Our union president was Michael. I met Prince Philip, Roger Moore and the first mp in the British House of Commons who happened to be an unmarried mother. Also met a few dignitaries from Southern Ireland. I have some snaps. I am now very nearly 81 and enjoy living with my old memories.

Conal Drain again, just wanted to say my very intellectual father went here, ended up being a mechanic from home, didn't even teach him right. That's what he said anyway. Haven't seen him in 10 years. Help.
Beautiful building.
Cool place to go if you like rocks

We spent five days here with Beyond Classrooms and couldn't have asked for a better person to spend our time with. Mark, The curator of The Miller Museum of Geology, is incredibly knowledgeable and personable, there wasn't a question he couldn't answer! It may be a small museum but the quality is fantastic. I have never held a meteorite before and to hold the largest ever recovered was an amazing experience! I was very impressed with the quality of the exhibits and attention to detail that has been put into them. The augmented reality sand box is unbelievable and just goes to show how much care and effort is put into this museum. A little gem, hidden in Queens but a real must see.
a great place to visit in Kingston. Totally underrated
Great !
Great space and very educational.

Great maritime museum, kid friendly. Interesting exhibit about the history and evolution of the Saint Lawrence Seaway. Hands on displays of various ship technologies, and spooky collection of artifacts from many of the great lake shipwrecks. Don't miss the chance to walk around the old coast guard ice breaker they have there, the Alexander Henry. We have been to many maritime museums but the freedom to explore the well preserved inner workings of the Alexander Henry is a truly unique experience. We came away with a better understand of how these big ships work and what life aboard would have been like.

This is an excellent museum. Our family of three thoroughly enjoyed it, including our 7 year old son. The main building is interesting as it is, but being able to tour the museum ship Alexander Henry just made our visit that much better. In the main building there are many different areas of interest and several hands on displays to keep the younger kids engaged. We spent a great deal of time in the waterways and shipping section, a big interest for our family. We also spent quite a bit of time on the Alexander Henry itself, enjoying being able to explore the ship at our leisure.

The Marine Museum and the Alexander Henry  (an imposing and magnificent Coast Guard Ship) are tributes not only to Kingston's history on Lake Ontario but to all the cities/towns on all of the Great Lakes.Over the years, as my grandsons grew from small boys to young men, we greatly enjoyed climbing onto the Alexander Henry and pretending that we were sailors out on one of the Great Lakes. Additionally,we were awed by the  collection of maps, pictures, paintings, historical papers and other Great Lakes memorabilia that are  protected in the museum. With the passing years my grandsons and I came to fully realize the importance of the Marine Museum in protecting the history of the Great Lakes. Now with great sorrow  I have to tell my  grandsons (who live in the US) that they will no longer be able to visit their friend ,the Alexander Henry, when they make their annual summer visit. The loss of the Marine Museum and the Alexander Henry is a tragedy for all of us who live in Kingston and who are proud of Kingston's history and a tragedy as well for all of those who  visited the Marine Museum and the Alexander Henry as children and who want to visit the museum and ship with their children/grandchildren.So,if you are visiting Kingston before August 23rd 2016, a visit the Museum is a must before its doors are closed forever.
This is a great museum if you like maritime history, but the ship is very interesting regardless. I am sorry to hear they are closing next month, but I recommend this to anyone until then.

Very disappointing they moved their location to a very small one room office space. Not until we gave a donation we were told this is it everything else is in storage.  There were only 5 items to look at.
Staff very helpful and knowledgeable and friendly. Was great to see same staff here and at the Pump House museum. We were remembered by staff and that was awesome.
Not sure what's there as was used to vote for the city of kingston.
Great place for kids
Not much variety in tools.
It was very nice
Enjoyed the area and the information from the visit.  Would recommend.  It's small but we'll displayed.
Great place for information on schools from generations ago
Wish they would finish rebuilding this historic place.
They are closed. The gym I got too is right next door.
Such a nice building it's a waste it's abandoned

It has grown so much since I was young..still beautiful. Lake Champlain . The only reason it was never listed as a great lake is because u can see the other side. But,it was big enough. I was born in VT. & spent many years on & off there. Lake Champlain is a place for BBQ'S, swimming & just  escaping. Having family & or friends fun.
We always love coming down here for a walk or just to play in the field with the kids. All year they have fun stuff going on usually, kids day, fourth of July with fireworks, tons of events.
The sun is shining, a breeze is blowing, and the lake is frozen over from shore to shore. It's an amazing day on the waterfront in Burlington!

This is a great place to watch the sunset. There are lots of show's during the summer,wide variety of shops, dispensary, ferry, awesome bike path, short ride to North Beach. There is a dog park, skatepark, lots of places to sit, wheelchair accessible and lots of grass to walk on, parking,boat ramps docks, playground.

Great spot on the Lake in downtown Burlington.  Convenient to parking, docks, a waterfront walking trail, Skinny Pancake crepe shop and the Leahy museum.  More than a bit cold in the winter but usually delightful in the summer and fall.  Short walk uphill to everything in downtown Burlington, a great spot to visit.
Sunnyside is an amazing park, I was there for the Coca Cola Classic Disc Golf Tournament. Awesome weekend.
Loved the park with the rolling hills and trees. Had a wonderful firepit and frisbee golf
Nice relaxing place to picnic or just chill and listen to nature.
Nice quiet place to camp without the noise. Secluded and safe
Nice playground equipment, lots of shade trees, not much traffic. Nice place to have a picnic and play.

Its a wonderful park with something for everyone. It has a great children's playground, with everything you would expect, with swings, sliders...sand pits, climbing frames and more challenging things for bigger kids...there is a skateboard park, and a duck pond. There are gardens full of flowers to enjoy, tennis,bowls and golf, put and play and crazy golf..tea shops toilets and ice cream and a bandstand

Probably the most amazing free outdoor children’s park I’ve ever been to. The range of equipment is vast! Several wonderful jungle gyms, with slides varying from beginners level all the way to this humongous tunnel slide which actually I’d quite like to get on myself!! 

With sandpits and climbing walls, a zip wire and so many swings, two double swings (for two children or an adult and a little one) one fully backed swing, lots of regular ones and even two of those big circle rope ones. 

There is also a cafe with toilets attached however I believe there is a charge for these so bring change.

There is also a nice ratio of sunny to shaded areas.

I’d happily bring the children here one morning with picnic blankets and food and spend the whole day !!

We had very nice time walking around the park. It's big, it's beautiful and have a lot of space for activities. Just take your blanket and picnic basket and head to Victoria Park for a lovely day :)
And Botanical Garden next to it is just magical. Perfect place to spend a day enjoying great weather, beautiful area and walking.

Lovely park for a wall and some fresh air. 
Had a picnic by the duck  pond, with my baby. Lots of ducks for children to feed. Lovely and clean, no litter anywhere,  lots  of benches to sit on.
We never went in the park, as my baby is only 11 weeks, but in time, we will. 
We'll  be back
Fabulous park, something for everyone. Family friendly play area which has a huge range of play equipment for all ages. Also love the botanic gardens and big open spaces for picnics
Absolutely amazing. The owner is fantastic. Love chatting with him!

Had the chicken hummus plate today (Dec 18 2018). Very big portion and juicy chicken. Was fresh and the man working was very polite. I highly recommend. Be sure to try the house dressing on the salad. Delicious.

Customer service is superb. Ordered via skipthedishes but they were out of the item I ordered. Being vegetarian I wasn't able to sub my pita. An employee there (maybe the owner) gave me a voucher for a free falafel for my next visit and wouldn't take payment from my friend who had ordered a chicken shwarma - completely generous on their part. Their garlic cream sauce is extra garlicky - yum.
Amazing blend of cultures and nice after a night out

Hi, I loved this place, but recently I got a donair chicken plate which entitled me to tomatoes, turnips and onions along with the meat, but all I got was the meat and I had to ask for the turnips and sadly forgot to ask for the onions and tomatoes so all I got was meat and turnips. I am not impressed with this service.

Great sandwiches and I love their breakfast. I eat here at least once a week. At lunch time the deli may seem really busy but just grab a number, the wait is never very long, plus it gives you time to pick what you want and even change your mind if need be.

I've always walked past this place and never got to try it til today. Yummy food & real friendly service! Enjoyed their house pate sandwich on housemade white bread although the Dijon mustard was overpowering. It's not a fancy place but if has a nice homey vibe

Very tasty, fresh, and well-prepared European classics at low prices. Friendly staff, spacious dining room, clean washrooms. Red cabbage and sauerkraut are standouts. Portions are very large. Berliner doughnuts and rum log and lemon cake are all excellent. There is limited free street parking in front and pay and display in back. You have to climb six stairs to enter from the back parking lot, but the double handrail is helpful if you have a mobility impairment. Washrooms are down a flight of stairs.
Atmosphere Nice quick service place Small but desert Yami  with cream caremal and vanilla flavor likes it .
Warm and tasty on a frigid day. ♥ 🥪 🥧
One of Kingston's hidden gems! Wok-In has a small storefront but has the best Thai/Cambodian food in town. The owners are so sweet & their portions are big! Very fair pricing but limited seating

Great food, awesome prices, and incredibly fast service. Owners are really friendly. Great spot to pop in for some truly authentic thai food. Some of the best i've ever had. All made fresh to order with huge portions.
Huge portions and great quality for amazing prices. Was full before I was even half done, will definitely be going back! 😊

I've been coming here for 25 years. The food is unmatched. Everything is made from scratch and the portions are huge. The place is tiny and you may have to wait for your food or a table, but it is so worth it. If you enjoy SE Asian food do not miss the Wok Inn.

A Kingston institution for good reason, though I think the phrase "you get what you pay for"really applies here. Very affordable, but don't expect anything fancy, especially for dining in.  We had a #14 (so-so) and a #15 (very good). Generous portions. Counter service, and the food is all cooked to order. The main problem is the meals take up to 50 minutes depending when you go, and don't come at the same time when you dine in.

Loved the wall of meme's in the men's washroom! The service was good, and apart from the big screen TV, the ambiance was nice, felt like a good pub. Nice selection of scotches. I was however sorely disappointed with the whiskey sour I ordered; made with some mass produced lime aid. Yech
This is great. Very affordable and pleasant staff. Makes a nice change from other restaurants/pubs. Where staff can be rude

This is the go to breakfast after partying at the same spot the night before! All fresh and local. You get a full breakfast (locally sourced) meal for the same price as a fast food drive thru sandwich by itself.
Great food   great selection of taps  maddy was a friendly attentive server   highly recommended!!!!!  Bangers and mash are fantastic
Awesome food and service st reasonable prices.

This is one of our favorite breakfast spots. Worth the wait when its busy. Very cozy small diner feel, but food as good as mom makes. Great service, food prepared fast, and lots of fresh selections. Also serve amazing lunch dishes. Cant be beat.
Great food, really reasonable prices. This was the first I've been here since the new renovation, and it's much nicer as far as atmosphere and roominess goes. Less of a wait too!

A straight forward, comfortable, and always delicious experience. Recently they made the restaurant way bigger but didn't mess with atmosphere or food at all. Great service, all day breakfast, and a favourite for locals, and visitors who decide to stop in.
Breakfast and lunch restaurant with a slight Greek influence. Feels a little like a diner but doesn't really look like one. Menu unfancy but well executed. Service good.

Good price, good food, good atmosphere.  Great place to sit down and enjoy breakfast.  Only problem is that 1 and 2 end up cutting down on 3, since the demand for tables makes it difficult to have a lazy breakfast.

This is probably the best place in Kingston to get Fajitas. They are pricey so be aware before you go. They brought back free chips and salsa so at least there is that.

Wait staff are usually pretty good although I have had a few run ins with not so good staff from time to time.

Best tip I can give is that if they are BUSY don't go there because chances are something will go wrong and you won't be happy. If they aren't lined up out the door though the Fajitas are definitely worth the price.
Great aged steak. I also liked the grilled chicken burger and their house salad is not just lettuce and cucumbers. However they serve food really slow.

This is great Texmex in Ontario, Canada.   The chips and salsa are complimentary to start your meal.   The salsa is very tasty with just the right amount of cilantro. Be careful not to over eat this appetizer as it's easy to spoil your main course!

Fajitas are what they are known for and they deliver.  The enchiladas are equally as tasty but many people never stray from the fajitas. 

Service is friendly and usually prompt.  This is not a fine dining experience but if you are looking for a casual Texmex meal, you can't go wrong!

I definitely love their rib. Their rib is soft enough to let you feel that the rib is melting on your mouth. Also, their server are friendly and fast. They always serve you the chip before and it tastes really good.

Some of the down side of this place is some dishes have relatively small portion that I still fell hungry after eating a combo even the price is OK. 
If you seating on the bar table, sometimes the lightning is relatively dark compare to the table.
The buffalo chicken and ceasar salad was excellent. A perfect end to a long day! Also, the service was excellent. I would recomment the Lone Star to everyone.

We had an amazing late night pizza stop here and were not disappointed! The pizza was really well made in traditional style and tasted amazing! The service was great, the staff friendly and the food fantastic! Lovely pizza and great service. Only negative is we felt there was too many tables so it was quite squashed. Best gourmet pizza you can find in Kingston. Amazing variety & amazing atmosphere. The restaurant is welcoming and the staff are always friendly. A must go in Kingston.

Good if you're into that kinda thing. Foods nothing to shake a stick at. Cocktails are great. The atmosphere was subtle but electric. Our server was on point with her knowledge, and very quick, but could have made the effort to build up a rapport with our table. All in all, good but not extrodanairy.

Every time I visit Kingston, Wooden Heads is on my short list of places to visit. The pizza is phenomenal, and the drinks are good. It's the first wood fire pizza I've eaten, and still one of the top. The desserts, though, is where Wooden Heads shine. Their chocolate lasagna is simply one of the greatest desserts I've ever had.

The restaurant itself is modern looking, along the waterfront, and cozy. Highly recommended for any outing, even just for dessert!

I have been to Woodenheads twice now, so I know it wasn't a mistake how good it was the first time. The second time going was just as delicious. The pizza I had had an apple butter sauce, caramelized onions, cheddar cheese and blackened chicken. The heat of the chicken was cut down by the sweetness of the sauce and overall I'd say it's one of the best pizzas that I have ever ate.

Coupled with a good beer from their diverse bar menu and beer selections it was a great experience and I will get back.

I'd strongly encourage making reservations as the restaurant is small and always packed!

Went there for the first time tonight and had a great experience! My boyfriend & I were seated at the bar because we did not have a reservation but even then we were lucky to be seated so I can't complain about that. The food and the service were amazing. The staff were very friendly and personable. As this is a gourmet restaurant the price was higher than your average pizza place but well worth it. We did not have to wait long for out food or drinks. I would definitely recommend making a reservation to anyone looking for a good time.

Nice ambiance, the pic below is of their cauliflower curry?? I added chicken, but under what definition is this curry? It was bland at best, with no hint of colour or aromatic spices. There were 9 of us ordering a variety of dishes, with 2 veggie options (this being one), a university town gastropub. Luckily students aren't too picky about the food, and quite frankly it was priced accordingly, which was fair. Lovely service staff hence the 4, but otherwise I'd really give it 3.5.

Kids menu is okay, nothing amazing but the kids enjoy it.

I can't recommend the burgers enough, they are awesome!  And the fries!

However, tonight I had the "Cauliflower curry".
This was a collection of cauliflower stems and assorted veg on a bed of unseasoned brown rice and quinoa, with what is listed as a "coconut curry" sauce.  This sauce was definitely coconut based.  It tasted as if the sauce had seen curry once, just in passing. But the coconut milk and curry never actually met in a saucepan.  

I literally knocked 2 stars off for this gross disappointment, it was that bad.

Save the $16, and order a burger.
This restaurant is a classic. It’s our go to choice for a neutral and comfortable dine-out dinner. Perfect service and delicious food every time.

My wife and I absolutely loved this place. It had a great cozy atmosphere , the food was excellent. No complaints at all ... 
The portions are pretty big too.
I tired the Buffalo cauliflower and it was amazing (so good I would maybe even choose it over wings).
Service was quick and very friendly.
I think its one of my new favorite places in Kingston for now.
My son's cheeseburger was awesome! My munchie platter was cold (deep fried mushrooms, onion rings). The waitress gave me a discount on the bill which was appreciated.
Wait staff is amazing. Food is good. Seating is very tight making the ambient noises and neighbouring conversations quite loud. All in all... we recommend it!

I came here for brunch and it's great. The portions are very large so you really do get what you're paying for. Food was absolutely delicious and the home fries were great. Very cozy atmosphere and great decorations. Our server came by to refill coffee which was nice.

Arrived at the restaurant only to find that our reservation had been somehow not written down. We were quickly and rudely dismissed by the waitress saying that there was no way they could accommodate us even though we had called hours in advance and were told we had a table. We were thrust onto the street to find a place to accommodate us Luckily, we were able to find another restaurant which was more than happy to give us the respect we deserved. Don't waste your time with a place treats its customers in such a disrespectful manner.

Most awful experience at this restaurant. We called to make a reservation and were assured that there was room. We get to the restaurant and the waitress somehow forgot to write our reservation down and refused to seat us even though we had proof of the reservation. On top of that she was extremely rude and dismissive, calling our questions redundant and a waste of time, when we were simply trying to figure out why they didn't have us down for the reservation we made. Spare yourself the headache with coming here and go to one of the many better restaurants on Princess St.

I've been in Kingston for 11 years. This is the one place that consistently has the worst food in the city of good food. DO NOT GO HERE. Quality matters, and this place just doesn't get it. So many better breakfast and brunch options around. Northside, Toast & Jam, Peter's. Even McDonald's has better bang for buck.

The food is usually sizzling hot, so I can confidently say it is freshly prepared every time. All the staff are really polite and caring. I order extra spicy and the servers usually warn me when I order my food. I have tried most of their dishes and like every single one of them. During peak hours I have waited upwards of 30 minutes to receive my order but the food has always been worth the wait. Highly recommend this place.

The Best Thai Soup anywhere period. Great family run business very friendly, good atmosphere. I always order Tom Yum (soup A) and Green Curry (soup E) . Soup E is the spicy one, I keep a box of tissues while I eat because it makes my nose run.

First time trying Cambodian food, it was recommended by a buddy who lives in Kingston. I had the golden chicken, it's spicy but excellent if you like spice! The Cambodian spice rolls are also excellent... Two of those is great for three people... We ordered 3 each and it was too much!

AMAZING. Leaving Kingston soon, and I'm sad I won't be able to eat here anymore. Huge portions, very reasonable prices.

Green curry, red curry, hot & sour soup, and golden chicken are all fantastic (as I'm sure the rest of the menu is too).

What to say except can someone please bottle the smell of this place and make it a perfume!? As soon as you step in the amazing aroma hits you and makes you hungry. The soups looked amazing and huge. I ordered something totally out of my wheelhouse and didn't care for it to much but that was just a poor choice I made. There was so much other great food I could have picked that was more to my taste.  Also for the tofu dishes, their tofu is super soft and melts in your mouth if that is not to your taste you can ask for it fried. Portions are huge, price is right, and the other people in my group LOVED their meals. The dining room is a little outdated but when you see the food getting pumped out of this kitchen you won't be looking at the decor.

I have had breakfast, lunch and takeout from Pan Chancho and it is always delicious!  They offer a variety of breads, cheeses, meats, warm and cold beverages and treats. During the warmer months they have a lovely patio and indoor seating while in the colder months they offer indoor seating.  When dining I noticed the reusable napkins and care packages they offer which I found to be smart, innovative and thoughtful.  Finally the staff are friendly and the prices are good for downtown eating and the quality of food and beverage.  Definitely a place to stop by when visiting Kingston!

Local icon so of course is very popular.

The bakery has great fresh bread and pastries. Price on the high side but it reflects the quality.

 The restraint at peak times such as weekend breakfast and brunch gets very busy but it's worth the wait. The menu for breakfast and brunch is extremely inventive with a lot of original items which are prepared very quickly and extremely tasty. Vegetarian options.

Although it's busy, there is ample space without feeling cramped and it's staff attentive. In the summer there's a great enclosed  patio at the back which expands the space and is extremely pleasant to be on.

Went here for breakfast with my family to the little cafe in the back. I don’t drink lactose and was able to get a latte made with oat milk which was delicious. I also had the blueberry pancake type thing which was delicious but was very filling. Everything on the menu looked delicious! Service was also great!

This is definitely one of the best places to eat in Kingston and we always ensure that we make a stop whenever we are in town. It goes without saying that all of the baked goods are excellent but the croissants are especially amazing. It also has plenty of culinary related gifts and premade meals as well so it's almost impossible to come out empty handed. Highly recommended.
A Kingston must-visit.  Everything is top notch and delicious.  Don't miss the biscotti/   Also, Pan Chancho bakes the best gluten free bread of all time.

Food is always terrific. Keep having to ask to turn the music down. It's not a nightclub.service is good to great but why does every restaurant serve the cappuccino 15 minutes before the dessert?? I hate that. Still, salads and entrees are the best in Kingston.

Friday evening for dinner with my daughter. We were seating and the chairs were so low it was a bit uncomfortable to eat. We both ordered pasta dishes and while the flavours were really good, I did find mine was a bit oily. There was a puddle of oil at the end in my bowl. We ordered a white chocolate raspberry dessert that was very good. We would return.
Excellent Italian food. Very posh and great location for your significant other or just having great food with family. Atmosphere was excellent. Highly recommend.
Absolutely a nice fine dining. Food was fantastic. Service was just as fantastic, we had apps, salad, main course and dessert, magnificent!

The food was incredible and came quickly. I had the pasta with the vodka sauce and my wife had a spicy shrimp spaghetti (can't remember the names of the dishes). The server was amazing and honestly I can't say enough good things about this place. It makes me want to up my own pasta game.

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.
